<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="531" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="47" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,332,357]" pageId="47" pageNumber="531">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new genus is named after Lizard 
<collectingCountry box="[773,844,332,357]" name="Iceland" pageId="47" pageNumber="531">Island</collectingCountry>
, where a major coral reef research station is located, the Lizard 
<collectingCountry box="[272,340,367,392]" name="Iceland" pageId="47" pageNumber="531">Island</collectingCountry>
Research Station, founded in 
<number box="[678,734,368,392]" pageId="47" pageNumber="531" value="1973.0">1973</number>
and run by the Australian Museum.
</paragraph>
